ca.uqac.lif.ecp.online

Class UnidirectionalTestDriver<T extends Event,C>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.uqac.lif.ecp.online.TestDriver<T,C>
      • ca.uqac.lif.ecp.online.UnidirectionalTestDriver<T,C>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The event type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Runnable

    public class UnidirectionalTestDriver<T extends Event,C>
extends TestDriver<T,C>
    Test driver that executes events sequentially and ignores any event sent back by the test hook. In other words, a unidirectional driver is not interactive: its behaviour does not depend on what the test hook does.
    Author:
    Sylvain Hallé

        protected List<Trace<T extends Event>> m_testSuite
        The test suite that the driver will replay. We allow this test suite to be an ordered set of traces, so that the user of the test driver can prioritize what sequences should be tried first.
